<p><font face="Arial Black"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>ADV Specification</font></font></font></center>

<p><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>• The
structural, static aspects of the interface objects using composition</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>•
The way in which interface objects are statically related with navigation
objects</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Use Configuration Diagrams to express these relationships</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>•
How they behave when reacting to external events;How they trigger navigation
and which interface transformations occur</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– ADV-charts used</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+1>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
• Allow to specify different states of interface objects</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+1>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
• The relationships between external events and the transitions shown</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+1>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
• Can be enriched with a Petri-net like notation that allows expressing
simple synchronization of concurrent activities</font></font></font>
